• Created Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) with Tensorflow that makes images like NFTs.
• Trained 2-convolution-layer discriminator and generator on 10,000 images over 700 generations.

Generates 64x64 images that could plausibly be NFTs from the Bored Ape collection, but are not. Uses a Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) with two convolution layers. Trained on around 10,000 images. Made for Hack The North 2022.
Created Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) with Tensorflow that makes images like NFTs.
Trained 2-convolution-layer discriminator and generator on 10,000 images over 700 generations.
• Watches Linux desktop notifications and run scripts for each notification.
• Made user configuration easy by creating documentation, tutorials, and manual pages.
I Spy Notify lets you watch Linux desktop notifications and run scripts for each notification. It's great for logging, displaying popups, and playing sounds.
Watches Linux desktop notifications and run scripts for each notification.
Implemented FreeDesktop Notifications standard using C, GTK+, and libdbus.
Made user configuration easy by creating documentation, tutorials, and manual pages.
• Developed single-page application to streamline completion of Ontario Court forms.
• Designed extensible form template system using Node.js, React, and Docxtemplater.
• Mentored team about website hosting, HTTPS authentication, CI/CD, and Docker.
Developed single-page application to streamline completion of Ontario Court forms.
Designed extensible form template system using Node.js, React, and Docxtemplater.
Mentored team about website hosting, HTTPS authentication, CI/CD, and Docker.
• Prototyped a mobile app that prepares random jogging routes based on user location and desired distance using React Native and OpenStreetMap.
• Visualised generated route using a native map interface with MapBox.
A mobile app that prepares random jogging routes based on user location and desired distance.
Prototyped a mobile app that prepares random jogging routes based on user location and desired distance using React Native and OpenStreetMap.
Visualised generated route using a native map interface with MapBox.
• Executes Common Lisp, Python 3, and Node.js in the shell for ad hoc scripting.
• User-focused design: cross-platform support, per-language configuration, stack-based evaluation.

Execute code in the command-line, usually as part of a shell script. Has utilities to read from standard input, write to standard output, and execute a configuration file. Expressions are pushed onto a stack, which enables code to be written linearly.
Executes Common Lisp, Python 3, and Node.js in the shell for ad hoc scripting.
User-focused design: cross-platform support, per-language configuration, stack-based evaluation.
• Provides interface using Emacs Lisp to traverse syntax tree for the Emacs text editor.
• Designed for user convenience: multiple cursor support, autocomplete, sticky highlighting.

This Emacs mode lets you traverse the Tree Sitter syntax tree. This package uses the built-in treesit package available starting from Emacs 29.
This package supports multiple-cursors.
Provides interface using Emacs Lisp to traverse syntax tree for the Emacs text editor.
Designed for user convenience: multiple cursor support, autocomplete, sticky highlighting.
• Enhanced messaging protocol of FreeSync certification tooling to improve communication rate between C++ host process and Arduino by 15%.
• Implemented extensible validation of FreeSync certification results using Python, supporting hundreds of tests in multiple data formats that evolved over 3+ years.
• Automated test orchestration, data collection, data storage, and visualization for Arduino-based latency measurement using C, Python, JavaScript, and D3.js.
• Modernized MS Access system with schema migrations and version control integration using Python, enabling simple deployment, releases, rollbacks, and parallel work for developers.
Enhanced messaging protocol of FreeSync certification tooling to improve communication rate between C++ host process and Arduino by 15%.
Implemented extensible validation of FreeSync certification results using Python, supporting hundreds of tests in multiple data formats that evolved over 3+ years.
Automated test orchestration, data collection, data storage, and visualization for Arduino-based latency measurement using C, Python, JavaScript, and D3.js.
Modernized MS Access system with schema migrations and version control integration using Python, enabling simple deployment, releases, rollbacks, and parallel work for developers.
• Created configurable jobs system using a CMS, AWS Lambda, Google Cloud, and Gatsby.
• Launched home and motor insurance platform using Node.js, MongoDB, GraphQL, Azure Service Bus, and Azure Functions.
• Implemented advanced frontend features in TypeScript and React, including pixel-perfect components, a nested modal system, DOM input focus behaviours, and snappy page transitions.
• Designed end-to-end regression and unit tests using Puppeteer and Jest.
• Enabled version information to be reported in analytics by creating a Webpack plugin.
Created configurable jobs system using a CMS, AWS Lambda, Google Cloud, and Gatsby.
Launched home and motor insurance platform using Node.js, MongoDB, GraphQL, Azure Service Bus, and Azure Functions.
Implemented advanced frontend features in TypeScript and React, including pixel-perfect components, a nested modal system, DOM input focus behaviours, and snappy page transitions.
Designed end-to-end regression and unit tests using Puppeteer and Jest.
Enabled version information to be reported in analytics by creating a Webpack plugin.
• Builds responsive HTML page for print, desktop, and mobile using Svelte and Strapi CMS.
• Identifies and sorts experience relevant to job posting using a pretrained language model.
• Extracts job posting and experience features in the browser using transformers.js.
